The smartest thing I did in my early twenties (as far as money goes) was
start investing. Not in specific stocks or early stage startups, but in the
market in general. I didn=E2=80=99t invest a whole lot of money, mostly bec=
ause I
didn=E2=80=99t have a whole lot of it in my early twenties. But I did inves=
t what I
could, with a regular cadence, every month.

Honestly, I=E2=80=99ve never been interested in specific investments, stock=
 markets
