ll high=E2=80=A6
I only vaguely know how that works.

I realized pretty quickly in my early twenties that simply saving money
doesn=E2=80=99t generate future wealth. If all my money just went into a ch=
equing
or even a savings account, it=E2=80=99d make either zero or a fraction of a
percentage of interest. And since money is worth less over time (hello
inflation!), if all I ever did was save money, I=E2=80=99d actually be losi=
ng
money. Note that I do think having *some* savings that are easily
