t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.01em!important">The conversation made me really have to think about what =
ideas I=E2=80=99d share with someone on building wealth. It was a little to=
ugh to verbalize at first, because talking about money can be pretty awkwar=
d. We=E2=80=99re not even taught much about money, investing or building fi=
nancial assets in grade school (which is a shame). I=E2=80=99m not a financ=
ial expert, so I won=E2=80=99t offer financial or investing advice (nor cou=
ntry-specific advice). But I=E2=80=99d like to share my thoughts on the sub=
ject as I apply them to my own life and circumstances, which you can take a=
nd think through for yourself. I=E2=80=99m also not going to get into the w=
eeds of what specifically to buy for investments, what company to use (I us=
e WealthSimple, since I know folks will ask), or how much you should invest=
=E2=80=94those are all things you can spend a tiny bit of time looking into=
, if your interest from this article is piqued.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"margin:10px 0;padding:0;margin-bottom:20px;color:#1=
