vetica Neue,Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif!importan=
t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.01em!important">The smartest thing I did in my early twenties (as far as =
money goes) was start investing. Not in specific stocks or early stage star=
tups, but in the market in general. I didn=E2=80=99t invest a whole lot of =
money, mostly because I didn=E2=80=99t have a whole lot of it in my early t=
wenties. But I did invest what I could, with a regular cadence, every month=
.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"margin:10px 0;padding:0;margin-bottom:20px;color:#1=
11!important;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,San Francisco,Hel=
vetica Neue,Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif!importan=
t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.01em!important">Honestly, I=E2=80=99ve never been interested in specific =
investments, stock markets or in doing a ton of research to understand them=
. So my investments have always been done in a way where I don=E2=80=99t ha=
ve to watch the markets, keep track of anything regularly, or spend a lot o=
f time figuring what to buy or sell and when. I check in on my investments =
maybe 4 times a year (when I remember), and mostly just out of curiosity. I=
 don=E2=80=99t buy low and sell high=E2=80=A6 I only vaguely know how that =
works.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"margin:10px 0;padding:0;margin-bottom:20px;color:#1=
11!important;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,San Francisco,Hel=
vetica Neue,Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif!importan=
t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.01em!important">I realized pretty quickly in my early twenties that simpl=
y saving money doesn=E2=80=99t generate future wealth. If all my money just=
 went into a chequing or even a savings account, it=E2=80=99d make either z=
ero or a fraction of a percentage of interest. And since money is worth les=
s over time (hello inflation!), if all I ever did was save money, I=E2=80=
=99d actually be losing money. Note that I do think having <em style=3D"fon=
t-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,San Francisco,Helvetica Neue,Helv=
etica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif!important;letter-spacing=
:0!important;line-height:1.6!important">some</em> savings that are easily a=
ccessible (i.e. =E2=80=9Cliquid=E2=80=9D) is important (a rainy day fund, i=
n case life gives me the middle finger). But bank accounts shouldn=E2=80=99=
t be the <em style=3D"font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,San Fran=
cisco,Helvetica Neue,Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif=
!important;letter-spacing:0!important;line-height:1.6!important">only</em> =
tool used.</p>

