t;font-size:17px;line-height:1.6!important;text-align:left;letter-spacing:-=
0.01em!important">Obviously, if you start investing early, you=E2=80=99ll h=
ave many more periods of your money doubling (every 10 years or so) in your=
 investment burrito. But it=E2=80=99s never too late to start, because even=
 if you are only generating wealth through labour for 10 years but investin=
g some of it, you=E2=80=99ll still probably (hopefully) double your money. =
If you only have 20 years to grow your investments, you=E2=80=99ll double y=
our money twice. Which is still four times better than just squirrelling yo=
ur money away under a mattress or in a normal bank account.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"margin:10px 0;padding:0;margin-bottom:20px;color:#1=
